message.content: cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.DC, cs.SY - The paper discusses congestion control and avoidance in high-speed networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses open-loop control versus feedback control, rate control versus window control, and router-based control versus source-based control, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of backpressure, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
